The paper discusses load balancing techniques for parallel algorithms executed over a P2P network, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of P2P networks also involves networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the dynamic properties of P2P networks, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.Distributed Systems). The use of under-utilized internet resources and high-performance computing is a topic in performance (cs.PF). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of parallel programs over the internet, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
